        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 9:28PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 928 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 6 miles northwest of Holyoke to 9 miles
north of Eckley, or extending from 6 miles northwest of Holyoke to
13 miles northeast of Yuma, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holyoke, Amherst and Pleasant Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
